title: Prescott leads Mississippi State over Louisiana Tech 45-20
text:
Sports Prescott leads Mississippi State over Louisiana Tech 45-20 Mississippi State defensive back Brandon Bryant (20) intercepts a pass and runs it back for a touchdown during the second half of a NCAA college football game against Louisiana Tech in Starkville, Miss., on Saturday, Oct. 17, 2015. Mississippi State ... more > By   
STARKVILLE, Miss. (AP) - Dak Prescott threw three touchdown passes and ran for another and Mississippi State beat Louisiana Tech 45-20 on Saturday. 
Prescott had scoring throws of 5, 20, and 12 yards, and finished 30 of 43 for 347 yards passing. He bullied in from the 2 for a touchdown to give Mississippi State (5-2) a 24-17 halftime lead. 
Mississippi State’s Brandon Bryant scored on a 73-yard interception return in the fourth quarter to cap the scoring. 
De’Runnya Wilson caught two touchdown passes, and Fred Brown had one for Mississippi State. Aeris Lavontae Williams ran for a 2-yard touchdown in the first quarter. 
Jeff Driskel threw two touchdown passes, and was 25 of 41 for 303 yards to lead Louisiana Tech (4-3). Trent Taylor caught 10 passes for 130 yards with one touchdown. 
Louisiana Tech jumped out to a 14-0 first quarter lead, and was up 17-10 midway through the second quarter.
